<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53125n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53125n">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53125n"> 125(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Kaundinia 1st / mo<font color="green">[u]</font>th,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">De ces cinq moines, <mark>Kaundinya, le premier</mark>, s&apos;approcha du Bienheureux, et lui dit: <p>&laquo;Je t&apos;ai &eacute;cout&eacute;, &ocirc; Ma&icirc;tre, et je te suivrai, si tu m&apos;en juges digne.</p> <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 111</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Kaudinia was the first of them to accept the Buddha as Master. </mm> </dd></dl>
